CAPE TOWN Eastern Cape police on Wednesday said they were investigating a case of murder following the fatal shooting of a 34-year-old male at Cambridge location.READ: Sex workers celebrate conviction of artist-murderer MthethwaIn a terse statement, police said on Tuesday at about 10 pm five armed men forced entry into the victim s shack before attacking him with sharp objects and shooting him. He sustained gunshot wounds on his upper body and died at the scene. Police are currently following strong leads and arrest is imminent, said police spokesperson Captain Mluleki Mbi.African News Agency